# n5_canonical.session
#
# Java twin of
# reticulate/tests/benchmarks/modularity/n5_canonical.sessiontype
#
# Canonical N5 (pentagon) counterexample to modularity. Per
# `feedback_java_python_parity` the BICA and reticulate copies of
# this file must stay character-identical in the type string (the
# single non-comment line at the bottom). Comment headers may
# differ in tone; the payload must not.
#
# Witness (state indices, under the quotient graph):
#     (top, u, v, w, bottom) = (1, 2, 3, 4, 0)
#
# Verification:
#   - ModularityChecker.check(Parser.parse(<type below>))
#         .isModular() == false
#   - certificate == "semantic"
#
# The N5 canonical fixture must NEVER be re-classified as modular by
# either tool. Any future refactor that flips this verdict is a
# regression in the modularity pipeline.
#
# Lines starting with `#` are comments. The first non-comment,
# non-empty line is the session type string.

&{a: &{x: &{y: end}}, b: &{z: end}}
